    "shortDescription": "<p>This spell functions as <i>suggestion</i>, except you can use it only to specify a condition that triggers a special activity, and the subject does not remember that you made the <i>suggestion</i>.</p><p>For example, you could use triggered <i>suggestion</i> on a palace guard to make him attack the king the next time he and the king are alone, and the guard would not remember the <i>suggestion</i> to do so until the trigger occurred.</p>",
